The paper focuses on introducing neuromodulation in deep neural networks to learn adaptive behaviors, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) since the paper proposes a new neural network architecture that is specifically designed to learn adaptive behaviors inspired by cellular neuromodulation. The paper also involves meta-reinforcement learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper's experimental results involve navigation benchmarks, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper's approach could also be applied to computer vision tasks, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
